2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with improving the performance of agents in reinforcement learning tasks, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new algorithm for policy improvement, which involves manipulating data structures and using algorithms to optimize policies. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with improving the performance of control systems (i.e., agents) in reinforcement learning tasks. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses f-divergences, which are a concept from information theory, to derive the policy update rules.
